nagios-plugins-ceph (1.5.6-6) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix OSD checks to find OSDs for a given hostname even when the IP for
    the hostname does not match the monitor IP (closes: #XXX)
    - Add helper functions to parse ceph config for hostname-to-IP mappings
    - Match OSDs by comparing all IPs from hostname with all IPs from OSD dump
    - Remove dependency on single DNS resolution IP
    - Affects check_ceph_osd and check_ceph_osd_db
  * Add -S/--status option to check_ceph_health to include ceph status output

 -- Bernd Zeimetz <bzed@debian.org>  Tue, 13 May 2025 15:00:00 +0200

nagios-plugins-ceph (1.5.6-5) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add cephadm support to all check scripts (from PR #88 by bluikko)
    - Add --cephadm and --admexe arguments to check_ceph_df, check_ceph_mgr,
      check_ceph_mon, check_ceph_osd, check_ceph_osd_db, check_ceph_osd_df, check_ceph_rgw
    - Prepend 'cephadm shell' to commands when --cephadm is used
    - Handle cephadm keyring with -v flag
    - Skip cephadm extra output lines in error handling

 -- Bernd Zeimetz <bzed@debian.org>  Tue, 13 May 2025 10:00:00 +0200

